This axe is fully hollow archtop, plays great, and sounds amazing with the original, highly sought-after goldfoil pickups. Harmony was at one point the largest manufacturer of guitars in the world. Of all Harmony models, Harmony hollowbodies tend to be the most sought-after by collectors. The H56/1 was released as part of the Rocket series in 1968 with two pickups, a three-way pickup switch, and four control knobs. Mostly Original.
